Package tage.rml

Class Vector4f

  • java.lang.Object
    • tage.rml.Vector4f
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<Vector4>, Vector4
    public final class Vector4f
extends java.lang.Object
implements Vector4
    An immutable single-precision floating point 4-component column vector. This vector is useful for transformations where homogeneous coordinates are needed.

    The homogeneous component w is set to 1 by default, unless explicitly specified otherwise, and is not taken into account during arithmetic operations. The homogeneous component is present to make operations with transform matrices possible.

    This means the input float[] { 1, 2, 3, 4 }; produces the following layout: 

     1
 2
 3
 4

    The implementation assumes the input arrays have enough elements to build the vector. When the input array does not have enough elements, an IndexOutOfBoundsException will be thrown. However, when the input array has extra elements, the extra data are ignored.

    Author:
    Raymond L. Rivera
